{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d309631b-70ab-473f-9920-8fbe7f5247bf","content":"Now I have a clear picture. Here's what needs to change for the v2 → v3 migration:\n\n1. **`.csproj`**: Update TFM (`net462` → `net8.0`), set `OutputType` to `Exe`, replace v2 packages with `xunit.v3`\n2. **`global.json`**: Switch test runner from `VSTest` to `Microsoft.Testing.Platform`\n3. **`SampleTests.cs`**: No changes needed (simple `[Fact]` + `Assert` API is compatible)\n\nLet me apply the changes:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01K4d9A4vvnpd2YpjTepwYeH","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Migrating xUnit v2 to v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01YK8135WiD29sy7NzxiT9tt","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-a988203753dd44308e48aa2947a9e63f/LegacyTests.csproj","old_str":"<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net462</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"18.3.0\" />\n    <PackageReference Include=\"xunit\" Version=\"2.9.3\" />\n    <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"2.8.2\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n</Project>","new_str":"<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3\" Version=\"1.1.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n</Project>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-a988203753dd44308e48aa2947a9e63f/LegacyTests.csproj."},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Ss8MVSLyqxuEzkbNimcXrs","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-a988203753dd44308e48aa2947a9e63f/global.json","old_str":"{\n  \"test\": {\n    \"runner\": \"VSTest\"\n  }\n}","new_str":"{\n  \"test\": {\n    \"runner\": \"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\"\n  }\n}"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-a988203753dd44308e48aa2947a9e63f/global.json."}],"interactionId":"84b346cf-358a-473c-a006-9e0107091414","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I understand the project. Let me plan the migration from xUnit.net v2 to v3:\n\n1. **Project file changes (LegacyTests.csproj)**:\n   - Update `TargetFramework` from `net462` to a supported TFM. xUnit.net v3 requires at least `net6.0` (or newer). Let me use `net8.0` as it's a current LTS.\n   - Replace xUnit v2 packages with xUnit v3 packages:\n     - Remove `xunit` (v2 meta-package)\n     - Remove `xunit.runner.visualstudio` (v2 runner)\n     - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` (not needed for v3)\n     - Add `xunit.v3` (v3 meta-package) - this includes the runner\n   - Change the output type to `Exe` since xUnit v3 test projects are standalone executables rather than class libraries\n\nFor the actual migration, the API stays largely the same—`[Fact]` and `[Theory]` attributes work unchanged, and `Assert` methods remain identical. The main differences are that v3 uses `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` for `dotnet test` integration instead of VSTest, and we need to target at least `net6.0`. The `xunit.v3` package handles the runner support directly, so we don't need separate runner packages. For xUnit v3 with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, I need to update the global.json runner configuration accordingly. The C# test code itself should stay mostly the same—the attributes and assertions don't change—but the real issue is that `net462` isn't supported by xUnit v3, so I'll need to target at least `net8.0` instead. I'll proceed with updating the project files and then build to validate everything works—if the xUnit version isn't quite right, the restore will flag it immediately.","outputTokens":1916,"requestId":"0836:2F47F1:CF15AE:F15E8D:69EAC873"},"id":"d0827d6a-d4c4-4923-90e6-42987fc2eadb","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:34:13.517Z","parentId":"1237bace-70b6-4413-b5d0-22f4a0a40b18"}
